import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    airport_names = ' '.join(data['name'].tolist())
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=480, height=480, margin=0).generate(airport_names)
    
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airport names?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
